                        Daniels
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v11</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d492</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">492</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-05-14T16:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-05-14T18:50:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-14T18:50:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-14T16:00:00-05:00" n="492" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.6363/5–1446: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName> [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-05-14T19:50:00-04:00" notBefore="1946-05-14T17:00:00-04:00" when="1946-05-14">undated</date>.]<lb/>[Received May 14, 1946—7:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>896. ReEmbstel 894, May 14, 5 p.m.<note n="85" xml:id="d492fn85">Not
                        printed.</note> This afternoon when presenting Admiral Bieri to President
                    Dutra latter spoke to me aside <pb facs="0563" n="545" xml:id="pg_545"/> and
                    said he had read the memorandum on petroleum policy I handed Gracie yesterday
                    afternoon. Dutra expressed satisfaction with memorandum and added that he
                    expected no unsurmountable difficulty in obtaining desired revision Brazilian
                    legislative provisions permitting foreign capital participation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
